review_blob: Nuts and strong scent of chocolate are present upon first whiff. Right away, you can tell that its a porter with flavor. Pours much like any other porter, minimal creamy head. A chocolate porter upon first sip, but a nice hint of vanilla follows in the aftertaste.

Labeled as an "Unfiltered Lager," and now I know why.  Too bad I poured it into a glass.  Cloudy golden, haze fills the glass as the yeast settles on the bottom.  Sorry but the yeast kinda looks funky.  I should have stayed with the filtered lager, I guess. 

Very light lemony aroma, would make a great summer beer.
